{"uuid": "ac9458c3-abc6-4e32-9843-7d72b757e6b8", "parentUuid": "4f0b69c2-2fe0-4ae9-b4ad-97eb616f1545", "sessionId": "ca5714a9-c057-4a11-9a5e-746865636173", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T06:49:50Z", "cwd": "/home/demo/pitch-factory", "version": "2.0.14", "isSidechain": true, "userType": "external", "type": "assistant", "requestId": "req_393e2b8606ed", "message": {"role": "assistant", "model": "claude-opus-4-8", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Flip it inside-out: don't document the casting machine — be it. THE CASTING: creators run the real audition gauntlet casting directors actually use — chemistry reads, a hot-mic house, network pitch tests — competing not for a trophy but for a genuine, contractually binding role on the network's next show."}], "usage": {"input_tokens": 4200, "output_tokens": 280, "cache_read_input_tokens": 1000, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0}}}
{"uuid": "132ca6e5-254c-44b2-9745-0347b176cfb9", "parentUuid": "db08fb42-6667-4259-b829-f3bcf46c63e7", "sessionId": "ca5714a9-c057-4a11-9a5e-746865636173", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T06:49:58Z", "cwd": "/home/demo/pitch-factory", "version": "2.0.14", "isSidechain": true, "userType": "external", "type": "assistant", "requestId": "req_f345599416d1", "message": {"role": "assistant", "model": "claude-opus-4-8", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "REVISE. The 'flips documentaries inside-out' claim is weak — the closest comps aren't documentaries, they're competition formats with the identical prize mechanic (Food Network Star, Scream Queens). There's no episode-by-stage grid, and the hot-mic house — one bounded event, or continuous surveillance? — is unspecified."}], "usage": {"input_tokens": 4600, "output_tokens": 300, "cache_read_input_tokens": 1000, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0}}}
{"uuid": "9b2a2716-35f3-4090-a94d-8417f621d1bc", "parentUuid": "ac9458c3-abc6-4e32-9843-7d72b757e6b8", "sessionId": "ca5714a9-c057-4a11-9a5e-746865636173", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T06:50:08Z", "cwd": "/home/demo/pitch-factory", "version": "2.0.14", "isSidechain": true, "userType": "external", "type": "assistant", "requestId": "req_b81a34541b0e", "message": {"role": "assistant", "model": "claude-opus-4-8", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reworked. Named the real comps — Food Network Star, Scream Queens — and differentiated them. Added an explicit funnel grid: 20 → 14 → 11 → 9 → 7 → 6 → 5 across EP2-7. The wired house is one bounded 24-hour hot-mic day; the rest of the season is a normal crewed multicam rig, not 24/7 surveillance."}], "usage": {"input_tokens": 5100, "output_tokens": 280, "cache_read_input_tokens": 1000, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0}}}
{"uuid": "ca953fc6-f8f6-4a5f-967d-14bd5ed405cc", "parentUuid": "132ca6e5-254c-44b2-9745-0347b176cfb9", "sessionId": "ca5714a9-c057-4a11-9a5e-746865636173", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T06:50:18Z", "cwd": "/home/demo/pitch-factory", "version": "2.0.14", "isSidechain": true, "userType": "external", "type": "assistant", "requestId": "req_0813b86b9581", "message": {"role": "assistant", "model": "claude-opus-4-8", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Better, and candid on cost and duty-of-care. Still REVISE: widen the comps to The Apprentice and Hell's Kitchen — both literally 'the prize is a real job'. Fix the funnel-portability math for other season types, and get a discrimination read on judging by casting 'type' before any real casting director is named."}], "usage": {"input_tokens": 5600, "output_tokens": 300, "cache_read_input_tokens": 1000, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0}}}
{"uuid": "95b37c44-2498-40a4-a023-08d70cb72659", "parentUuid": "9b2a2716-35f3-4090-a94d-8417f621d1bc", "sessionId": "ca5714a9-c057-4a11-9a5e-746865636173", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T06:50:30Z", "cwd": "/home/demo/pitch-factory", "version": "2.0.14", "isSidechain": true, "userType": "external", "type": "assistant", "requestId": "req_c54d7f82548e", "message": {"role": "assistant", "model": "claude-opus-4-8", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "v3. Comps widened to the whole 'real job as prize' lane — Apprentice, Hell's Kitchen, ANTM's actual prize (an agency contract, not a trophy) — alongside the Idol / X Factor 'real contract' DNA. The funnel now scales by a stated rule to the downstream show's actual cast-size need."}], "usage": {"input_tokens": 6000, "output_tokens": 270, "cache_read_input_tokens": 1000, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0}}}
